-  the safety net (`spec/v0/04-task-protocol.md` §3). The UI must not
-  retry claims server-side for a user who doesn't return — that
-  would mask the issue.
+- **Stranded human claims.** A user who claims a plan task and
+  closes the tab leaves the claim token only in their session
+  cookie. Mitigation: the UI sets an explicit
+  `expires_at = now + --claim-ttl-seconds` on every claim, so the
+  task-store's `expired` reclaim cause picks abandoned claims back
+  up automatically (spec/v0/04-task-protocol.md §5). Phase 9e adds
+  an explicit operator-reclaim button as a faster recovery path.
+  The UI must not retry claims server-side for a user who doesn't
+  return — that would mask the issue.
+- **Partial proposal writes.** The Phase 1 → Phase 2 → Phase 3
+  ordering in §C narrows the unsafe window to "ready proposals
+  not yet referenced by a submitted plan task," but does not
+  eliminate it. A spec-level fix (atomic `mark_ready_and_submit`)
+  is out of scope for Phase 9 chunk 1; the implementation
+  surfaces orphaned proposal IDs to the operator on Phase-3
+  failure so they can reclaim and retry.
+- **Experiment-config drift.** The UI loads its own copy of
+  `experiment-config.yaml`; if it diverges from the
+  task-store-server's copy, planner-side validation could pass on
+  inputs the evaluator's metrics_schema would later reject. Phase
+  12's control plane is the right fix; for now the start-up
+  `experiment_id` mismatch check catches the loud cases.
+- **CSRF / cookie attribute regressions.** The cookie/CSRF policy
+  is enforced by `tests/test_security_invariants.py`. Any change
+  that loosens an attribute or skips the CSRF check breaks the
+  test, by design.
+- **Bearer-token leak via templating.** Mitigated by the
+  bearer-leak unit test, the JSON-line log redaction, and the
+  manual `grep -r "$EDEN_SHARED_TOKEN"` verification step. A
+  reviewer should still spot-check any new template that
+  receives the configuration object.
